---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import TrustBlock from "../components/TrustBlock.astro";
import FoundingCTA from "../components/FoundingCTA.astro";
import PricingBadge from "../components/PricingBadge.astro";

const title = "AI Readiness Audit — From $1,000 | Ascend Griffin";
const description =
  "AI readiness audit for non-technical founders. Get a clear, vendor-independent read on your AI tools, vibe-coded code, and tech risk. From $1,000 · 5-14 days.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <Nav />
  <main class="svc">
    {/* ── Hero ────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */}
    <section class="svc-hero">
      <div class="svc-grid">
        <aside class="svc-rail">
          <div class="rail-marker">01</div>
          <div class="rail-label">Audit</div>
        </aside>

        <div class="svc-hero-body">
          <p class="svc-epigraph">
            "Most IT projects don't fail because of bad code.<br />
            They fail because no one was reading on the client's side."
          </p>

          <h1 class="svc-h1">
            Read your AI build for <em>what it really is</em> —<br />
            before it costs another $50K.
          </h1>

          <p class="svc-lede">
            Vibe-coded prototype. Vendor proposal on your desk. Existing AI feature that quietly stopped working. Before you commit the next round of capital — a structured read from someone with no financial interest in the build decision.
          </p>

          <PricingBadge price="from $1,000" duration="5-14 days" />

          <div class="svc-hero-cta">
            <a
              href="#book"
              class="svc-btn-primary"
              data-modal="booking"
              data-subject="audit"
              data-source="ai-audit-hero"
            >
              Request audit →
            </a>
            <a href="#deliverables" class="svc-btn-ghost">See what you get →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ── Trust ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── */}
    <TrustBlock />

    {/* ── Who this is for ────────────────────────────────────────── */}
    <section class="svc-section" id="who">
      <div class="svc-grid">
        <aside class="svc-rail">
          <div class="rail-marker">02</div>
          <div class="rail-label">Who this is for</div>
        </aside>

        <div class="svc-section-body">
          <h2 class="svc-h2">Two situations I read for.</h2>

          <article class="icp-card">
            <header class="icp-header">
              <span class="icp-num">A</span>
              <h3 class="icp-title">The vibe coder who shipped something real.</h3>
            </header>
            <p>
              You built a working prototype in Cursor, v0, Lovable, or Claude. Twenty paying users. A few features in flight. And a growing sense that something in the foundation isn't right — but you can't read the codebase to confirm it. You don't need a developer right now. You need someone who can tell you: <em>what holds, what doesn't, and what the path to production-readiness actually looks like.</em>
            </p>
          </article>

          <hr class="hairline" />

          <article class="icp-card">
            <header class="icp-header">
              <span class="icp-num">B</span>
              <h3 class="icp-title">The non-technical commissioner staring at three proposals.</h3>
            </header>
            <p>
              Three vendor quotes on your desk. $45K to $120K for what sounds like the same project. One vendor confident, two vague, all three professionally persuasive. Without a technical background it's nearly impossible to tell which quote is honest, which is padded, and which will grow by 40% the moment a change request lands. <em>The job here is to read those proposals the way the vendor wrote them</em> — and translate that into a clear recommendation.
            </p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ── Deliverables ───────────────────────────────────────────── */}
    <section class="svc-section svc-section-deliverables" id="deliverables">
      <div class="svc-grid">
        <aside class="svc-rail">
          <div class="rail-marker">03</div>
          <div class="rail-label">What you receive</div>
        </aside>

        <div class="svc-section-body">
          <h2 class="svc-h2">Five concrete artifacts.</h2>
          <p class="svc-section-lede">
            Not a slide deck. Not a "framework." Five things your team can act on the morning after our final call.
          </p>

          <ol class="ledger">
            <li class="ledger-item">
              <span class="ledger-num">01</span>
              <div class="ledger-content">
                <h4>Plain-English read of what's been built.</h4>
                <p>Codebase, vendor proposal, or AI feature — what holds, what doesn't, in priority order. No jargon you have to Google.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="ledger-item">
              <span class="ledger-num">02</span>
              <div class="ledger-content">
                <h4>Specific risks with dollar-impact tags.</h4>
                <p>"This contract clause will cost you ~$8K in month 3" — not "this is something to consider." Numbers attached where I can attach them.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="ledger-item">
              <span class="ledger-num">03</span>
              <div class="ledger-content">
                <h4>A comparison framework if you're choosing.</h4>
                <p>Build vs. buy. Rewrite vs. patch. Vendor A vs. vendor B. Each option scored on the criteria that actually matter to your business.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="ledger-item">
              <span class="ledger-num">04</span>
              <div class="ledger-content">
                <h4>A one-page summary your team can act on.</h4>
                <p>Written so it makes sense to non-technical readers — co-founders, board members, finance — without me having to be in the room.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="ledger-item">
              <span class="ledger-num">05</span>
              <div class="ledger-content">
                <h4>A 60-minute walk-through call.</h4>
                <p>Real questions answered in real time. Not a Slack thread that goes cold on Friday.</p>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ── Not included ───────────────────────────────────────────── */}
    <section class="svc-section svc-section-muted" id="not">
      <div class="svc-grid">
        <aside class="svc-rail">
          <div class="rail-marker">04</div>
          <div class="rail-label">Not included</div>
        </aside>

        <div class="svc-section-body">
          <h2 class="svc-h2">What this audit is <em>not</em>.</h2>
          <p class="svc-section-lede">
            Saving us both a wasted first call.
          </p>

          <ul class="exclude">
            <li><span class="exclude-mark">—</span><span><strong>Code refactor.</strong> I read. I don't rewrite.</span></li>
            <li><span class="exclude-mark">—</span><span><strong>Vendor introductions.</strong> Separate engagement, scoped differently.</span></li>
            <li><span class="exclude-mark">—</span><span><strong>Long-term oversight.</strong> That's Project Support — also separate.</span></li>
            <li><span class="exclude-mark">—</span><span><strong>Pitch deck review or fundraising help.</strong> Not what this is, and there are better people for that.</span></li>
            <li><span class="exclude-mark">—</span><span><strong>"Tell me what I want to hear."</strong> If you're looking for validation rather than verification, I'm definitely not the right read.</span></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ── FAQ ────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */}
    <section class="svc-section" id="faq">
      <div class="svc-grid">
        <aside class="svc-rail">
          <div class="rail-marker">05</div>
          <div class="rail-label">Common questions</div>
        </aside>

        <div class="svc-section-body">
          <h2 class="svc-h2">Three questions that come up.</h2>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>
              <span class="faq-q">How is this different from a code review?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-a">
              <p>A code review tells you whether code is well-written. This tells you whether the <em>project decision</em> is well-made. Different question, different answer. If you also need a code review, I can point you to specialists who do that better than I would.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>
              <span class="faq-q">What if you find nothing wrong?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-a">
              <p>That happens — and it's a useful answer too. You walk away with documented confidence that the path you're on holds. Most founders who pay for an outside read are actually looking for exactly that: the right to commit, with someone independent on record saying it checks out.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary>
              <span class="faq-q">Do you sign an NDA?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-a">
              <p>Yes. Mutual NDA template sent within 24 hours of request. Nothing from your project enters my content, my comms, or another conversation without your written approval.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    {/* ── Founding CTA ───────────────────────────────────────────── */}
    <FoundingCTA service="audit" spotsLeft={2} />
  </main>
  <Footer />

  <script
    type="application/ld+json"
    set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "Service",
      name: "AI Readiness Audit",
      provider: {
        "@type": "Person",
        name: "Taras Smaliukh",
        url: "https://ascendgriffin.org/about/",
      },
      areaServed: ["Ukraine", "United Kingdom", "Germany", "United States"],
      description,
      offers: {
        "@type": "Offer",
        priceCurrency: "USD",
        price: "1000",
        priceSpecification: {
          "@type": "PriceSpecification",
          minPrice: 1000,
          priceCurrency: "USD",
        },
      },
      serviceType: "Independent technical audit for non-technical founders",
    })}
  />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ── Page shell ──────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .svc {
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse at top right, rgba(184, 135, 58, 0.04), transparent 50%),
      radial-gradient(ellipse at bottom left, rgba(184, 135, 58, 0.03), transparent 40%),
      var(--bg-0);
    min-height: 100vh;
  }

  .svc-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 180px 1fr;
    gap: 64px;
    max-width: 1120px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 var(--gutter);
  }
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .svc-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 24px;
      padding: 0 var(--gutter-sm);
    }
  }

  /* ── Floating section rail (number + label) ──────────────────── */
  .svc-rail {
    position: sticky;
    top: 88px;
    align-self: start;
    height: fit-content;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--text-1);
    padding-top: 14px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .svc-rail {
      position: static;
      display: flex;
      align-items: baseline;
      gap: 12px;
      padding-top: 8px;
    }
  }
  .rail-marker {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-1);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    line-height: 1;
  }
  .rail-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--text-3);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    margin-top: 6px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .rail-label { margin-top: 0; }
  }

  /* ── Hero ────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .svc-hero {
    padding: 80px 0 56px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .svc-hero { padding: 48px 0 32px; }
  }
  .svc-epigraph {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--text-3);
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0 0 32px;
    padding-left: 18px;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--accent);
    max-width: 50ch;
  }
  .svc-h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(40px, 5.5vw, 68px);
    line-height: 1.04;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    color: var(--text-1);
    margin: 0 0 28px;
    font-weight: 700;
    max-width: 18ch;
  }
  .svc-h1 em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--editorial);
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .svc-lede {
    font-size: 19px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text-2);
    margin: 0 0 32px;
    max-width: 56ch;
  }
  .svc-hero-cta {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 16px;
    align-items: center;
    margin-top: 12px;
  }
  .svc-btn-primary {
    background: var(--bg-ink);
    color: var(--text-on-ink);
    padding: 16px 28px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 15px;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    transition: background var(--dur-fast) var(--ease);
  }
  .svc-btn-primary:hover { background: #2a2724; }
  .svc-btn-ghost {
    color: var(--text-1);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--accent);
    padding-bottom: 2px;
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 500;
    transition: color var(--dur-fast) var(--ease);
  }
  .svc-btn-ghost:hover { color: var(--accent-pressed); }

  /* ── Section frame ──────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .svc-section {
    padding: 80px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-1);
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .svc-section { padding: 48px 0; }
  }
  .svc-section-muted { background: var(--bg-1); }

  .svc-h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(28px, 3.5vw, 40px);
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    color: var(--text-1);
    margin: 0 0 16px;
    font-weight: 700;
    max-width: 22ch;
  }
  .svc-h2 em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--editorial);
  }
  .svc-section-lede {
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text-2);
    margin: 0 0 40px;
    max-width: 56ch;
  }

  /* ── ICP cards ──────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .icp-card { margin-bottom: 32px; }
  .icp-card:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .icp-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .icp-num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--accent-pressed);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    background: var(--accent-subtle);
    padding: 4px 10px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    line-height: 1;
  }
  .icp-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(20px, 2.4vw, 24px);
    line-height: 1.25;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    color: var(--text-1);
    margin: 0;
    font-weight: 600;
    flex: 1;
  }
  .icp-card p {
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--text-2);
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 65ch;
  }
  .icp-card p em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-1);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .hairline {
    border: 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-1);
    margin: 32px 0;
  }

  /* ── Ledger (deliverables) ──────────────────────────────────── */
  .ledger {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--text-1);
  }
  .ledger-item {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 64px 1fr;
    gap: 24px;
    padding: 28px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-1);
    align-items: start;
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .ledger-item {
      grid-template-columns: 40px 1fr;
      gap: 16px;
      padding: 24px 0;
    }
  }
  .ledger-num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 24px;
    color: var(--accent-pressed);
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }
  .ledger-content h4 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 18px;
    color: var(--text-1);
    margin: 0 0 8px;
    line-height: 1.35;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
  }
  .ledger-content p {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--text-2);
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 60ch;
  }

  /* ── Exclude list ───────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .exclude {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .exclude li {
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: 16px;
    padding: 14px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--border-1);
    color: var(--text-2);
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .exclude li:last-child { border-bottom: 0; }
  .exclude-mark {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    color: var(--text-4);
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .exclude strong {
    color: var(--text-1);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  /* ── FAQ ────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .faq-item {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-1);
    padding: 4px 0;
  }
  .faq-item:last-of-type { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-1); }
  .faq-item summary {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 24px;
    cursor: pointer;
    padding: 24px 0;
    list-style: none;
  }
  .faq-item summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  .faq-q {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 19px;
    color: var(--text-1);
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.35;
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
  }
  .faq-toggle {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 22px;
    color: var(--accent-pressed);
    line-height: 1;
    transition: transform var(--dur-base) var(--ease);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .faq-item[open] .faq-toggle {
    transform: rotate(45deg);
  }
  .faq-a {
    padding: 0 0 24px;
  }
  .faq-a p {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--text-2);
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 65ch;
  }
  .faq-a p em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-1);
  }
</style>
